2025-03-02T10:10:56.304180Z  INFO docgen: Step 2 prompt content:
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304204Z  INFO docgen:   Line 1: You are a top-tier AI assistant. You have received the following initial ideation from the user:
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304217Z  INFO docgen:   Line 2: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304229Z  INFO docgen:   Line 3: Okay, here's a completed example of the Initial Project Ideation template, focusing on a project I think would be interesting and useful.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304241Z  INFO docgen:   Line 4: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304253Z  INFO docgen:   Line 5: ## Project Name:
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304265Z  INFO docgen:   Line 6: Recipe Radar
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304276Z  INFO docgen:   Line 7: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304288Z  INFO docgen:   Line 8: ## Project Description:
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304300Z  INFO docgen:   Line 9: Recipe Radar is a web application that helps users discover new recipes based on ingredients they already have, dietary restrictions, and cuisine preferences. It solves the problem of "what to cook tonight" by providing personalized recipe recommendations, reducing food waste, and inspiring culinary exploration.  What makes it unique is its focus on minimizing waste by prioritizing recipes that utilize ingredients the user already possesses. It also incorporates a social sharing component allowing users to share their own recipe creations. The core functionalities include ingredient input, dietary filter application, cuisine selection, recipe recommendation, recipe saving/organization, and community recipe sharing.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304317Z  INFO docgen:   Line 10: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304329Z  INFO docgen:   Line 11: ## Key Features:
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304341Z  INFO docgen:   Line 12: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304353Z  INFO docgen:   Line 13: - **Intelligent Ingredient Matching:**  Users can input ingredients they have on hand, and the application will prioritize recipes that utilize those ingredients, displaying a percentage of matching ingredients for each recipe.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304365Z  INFO docgen:   Line 14: - **Dietary and Allergy Filtering:**  Robust filtering options to accommodate a wide range of dietary restrictions (vegetarian, vegan, gluten-free, keto, paleo, etc.) and common allergies (nuts, dairy, soy, etc.).
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304377Z  INFO docgen:   Line 15: - **Cuisine and Dish Type Selection:**  Users can filter by cuisine (Italian, Mexican, Asian, etc.) and dish type (appetizer, main course, dessert, etc.) to narrow down their recipe options.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304390Z  INFO docgen:   Line 16: - **Personalized Recipe Recommendations:**  An algorithm that learns user preferences over time based on saved recipes, ratings, and search history to provide increasingly relevant recommendations.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304403Z  INFO docgen:   Line 17: - **Recipe Saving and Organization:**  Users can save recipes to their account and organize them into custom collections (e.g., "Quick Weeknight Meals," "Desserts to Try").
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304415Z  INFO docgen:   Line 18: - **Community Recipe Sharing & Rating:** Users can create profiles and share their own recipes with the community, and rate other user submitted recipes.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304427Z  INFO docgen:   Line 19: - **Nutritional Information Display:** Integration with a nutrition API to display detailed nutritional information (calories, macros, micronutrients) for each recipe.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304452Z  INFO docgen:   Line 20: - **Shopping List Generation:** Automatically generates a shopping list based on the ingredients needed for a selected recipe that the user doesn't already have.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304465Z  INFO docgen:   Line 21: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304477Z  INFO docgen:   Line 22: ## Target Users:
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304488Z  INFO docgen:   Line 23: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304499Z  INFO docgen:   Line 24: - **Home Cooks:** Individuals who enjoy cooking at home but struggle with meal planning and finding new recipe ideas.  Their needs include easy access to diverse recipes, the ability to utilize existing ingredients, and dietary-friendly options.  Their pain points include recipe overload, difficulty finding recipes that meet their dietary needs, and wasting food due to lack of planning.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304511Z  INFO docgen:   Line 25: - **Busy Professionals:**  Individuals with limited time for meal planning and cooking who need quick, easy, and healthy recipe options.  Their needs include recipes with short cooking times, minimal ingredients, and customizable portion sizes.  Their pain points include relying on takeout or processed foods due to time constraints and lack of inspiration.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304523Z  INFO docgen:   Line 26: - **Foodies:**  Enthusiastic cooks who are always looking for new and exciting recipes to try.  Their needs include access to a wide variety of cuisines and cooking techniques, and a platform for sharing their own culinary creations.  Their pain points include sifting through irrelevant recipes and not having a centralized place to organize their culinary inspiration.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304536Z  INFO docgen:   Line 27: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304548Z  INFO docgen:   Line 28: ## Success Criteria:
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304564Z  INFO docgen:   Line 29: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304574Z  INFO docgen:   Line 30: - **User Engagement:**  Daily/Monthly Active Users (DAU/MAU), average session duration, number of recipes saved per user, community recipe contributions.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304584Z  INFO docgen:   Line 31: - **Recipe Discovery:**  Click-through rate on recommended recipes, percentage of users who save recommended recipes, positive ratings for the recommendation algorithm.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304595Z  INFO docgen:   Line 32: - **User Retention:**  Percentage of users who return to the app on a weekly/monthly basis.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304606Z  INFO docgen:   Line 33: - **Positive User Feedback:** Measured through in-app feedback forms, app store reviews, and social media mentions.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304616Z  INFO docgen:   Line 34: - **Community Growth:** Number of user registrations, and consistent upload of new user submitted recipes.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304626Z  INFO docgen:   Line 35: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304636Z  INFO docgen:   Line 36: ## Technical Constraints (Optional):
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304647Z  INFO docgen:   Line 37: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304657Z  INFO docgen:   Line 38: - **Technology stack:**  Frontend: React.js; Backend: Node.js with Express.js; Database: MongoDB; API Integrations: Edamam Nutrition API, Spoonacular API (for initial recipe data, later prioritize community contributions)
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304669Z  INFO docgen:   Line 39: - **Performance requirements:**  Fast loading times for recipe pages (under 2 seconds), efficient search functionality, scalable architecture to handle a growing user base.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304680Z  INFO docgen:   Line 40: - **Compatibility requirements:**  Cross-browser compatibility (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge), responsive design for mobile devices, secure data storage and user authentication.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304692Z  INFO docgen:   Line 41: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304704Z  INFO docgen:   Line 42: ## Timeline (Optional):
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304716Z  INFO docgen:   Line 43: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304727Z  INFO docgen:   Line 44: - **Phase 1 (3 months):**  Core functionality development:  Ingredient input, dietary/cuisine filtering, basic recipe recommendation, user registration/login.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304739Z  INFO docgen:   Line 45: - **Phase 2 (2 months):**  Personalized recommendation algorithm implementation, recipe saving and organization features.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304752Z  INFO docgen:   Line 46: - **Phase 3 (1 month):**  Nutritional information display integration, shopping list generation.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304764Z  INFO docgen:   Line 47: - **Phase 4 (2 months):**  Community recipe sharing, user profiles, rating/commenting features.  Refinement based on initial user feedback.
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304776Z  INFO docgen:   Line 48: 
2025-03-02T10:10:56.304787Z  INFO docgen:   Line 49: 
