2025-03-02T10:44:36.811128Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 7: 
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811143Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 8: **1. Introduction**
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811157Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 9: 
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811175Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 10: This document outlines the requirements for a Flutter application that allows users to view PDF documents on mobile devices (iOS and Android). The application will leverage the `pdfx` package (or a suitable alternative if performance issues arise) for PDF rendering and manipulation. This document serves as the primary reference for development, testing, and product management.
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811190Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 11: 
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811205Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 12: **2. Goals**
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811221Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 13: 
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811235Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 14: *   Provide a user-friendly, efficient, and reliable way to view PDF documents on mobile devices.
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811252Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 15: *   Offer core PDF viewing functionalities, including zoom, navigation, search (with highlighting), and text selection/copy.
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811267Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 16: *   Ensure optimal performance and stability across a range of devices (low, mid, and high-end) and a variety of PDF files (small, large, complex).
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811283Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 17: *   Prioritize a clean and intuitive user interface, adhering to platform-specific design guidelines (Material Design for Android, Human Interface Guidelines for iOS).
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811297Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 18: 
2025-03-02T10:44:36.811312Z  INFO docgen::pipeline:   Line 19: **3. Target Audience**
